Perhaps Pierre? Monique?

315
00:26:06,727 --> 00:26:08,718
You have the face of an angel.

316
00:26:08,807 --> 00:26:12,083
I'm delighted to find
the mind is a little devil.

317
00:26:13,127 --> 00:26:14,606
Look, mister.

318
00:26:14,687 --> 00:26:18,157
This is gonna get you nowhere.
I am waiting to meet my fiance.

319
00:26:18,247 --> 00:26:21,444
If he sees you bothering me,
even talking to me,

320
00:26:21,527 --> 00:26:24,405
he's gonna walk over here and he...

321
00:27:10,287 --> 00:27:12,847
What are you doing here?
You only work the metro.

322
00:27:12,927 --> 00:27:16,522
No more. With this suit, I'm a new man.

323
00:27:24,167 --> 00:27:26,158
Charlie?

324
00:27:28,767 --> 00:27:30,962
You said you'd give me a ride.

325
00:27:31,047 --> 00:27:35,120
- You said... Where are we?
- In your hotel. I'll take you to your room.

326
00:27:35,207 --> 00:27:37,960
I don't have a room.
Someone has taken my room.

327
00:27:38,047 --> 00:27:41,119
Someone in four-inch heels, a red dress...

328
00:27:42,327 --> 00:27:45,364
Oh, my God! My bags!

329
00:27:45,447 --> 00:27:47,677
- What?
- My bags are gone.

330
00:27:47,767 --> 00:27:50,725
What do you mean, they are gone?
How can they be gone?

331
00:27:50,807 --> 00:27:55,278
What are you looking under there for?
I didn't lose my keys. I lost my suitcase.

332
00:27:55,367 --> 00:27:58,006
Where did you put them down? Think.

333
00:27:58,087 --> 00:28:01,921
I fainted right there.
My money, my passport.

334
00:28:02,007 --> 00:28:03,884
- My vitamins.
- May I be of service?

335
00:28:07,527 --> 00:28:09,995
Yeah, you tell him.

336
00:28:10,087 --> 00:28:12,043
How could you let this happen?

337
00:28:12,127 --> 00:28:15,039
- What is your problem? They're my bags.
- But you could...

338
00:28:15,127 --> 00:28:18,278
I'm upset because it is my country
and this is a scandal.

339
00:28:18,367 --> 00:28:21,279
- Do you remember anything?
- I was sitting here.

340
00:28:21,367 --> 00:28:24,598
That guy came and talked to me
and then...

341
00:28:25,087 --> 00:28:27,282
I saw Charlie.

342
00:28:27,367 --> 00:28:29,517
Here we go again. Here, sit.

343
00:28:29,607 --> 00:28:32,440
Breathe in. Breathe out. Breathe in.

344
00:28:32,527 --> 00:28:35,200
I'm breathing. All men are bastards.

345
00:28:35,287 --> 00:28:37,482
Not all. Some are just trying to help.

346
00:28:37,567 --> 00:28:42,277
I never thought I'd be the type to say
this, but it's true. All men are bastards.

347
00:28:42,367 --> 00:28:44,597
The guy who was talking to you. He was...

348
00:28:44,687 --> 00:28:47,918
A bastard.
A Eurotrash in Armani kind of bastard.

349
00:28:48,007 --> 00:28:50,202
In a black suit with a yellow shirt?

350
00:28:50,287 --> 00:28:51,606
Yeah.

351
00:28:51,687 --> 00:28:54,042
You know him? Of course you know him.

352
00:28:54,127 --> 00:28:56,687
All you bastards know each other.

353
00:28:57,047 --> 00:28:59,515
Bastard.

354
00:29:01,407 --> 00:29:03,716
All right. You wait here.

355
00:29:03,807 --> 00:29:08,198
I go get a... my car
and we go get your stuff, OK?

356
00:29:48,607 --> 00:29:52,805
- So who is this guy who stole my bags?
- Bub.

357
00:29:52,967 --> 00:29:55,606
- Bub?
- No. Bub.

358
00:29:55,687 --> 00:29:58,121
Bub, like Bub Dylan.

359
00:29:58,207 --> 00:30:01,040
- Bob.
- Bob.

360
00:30:01,327 --> 00:30:03,887
- Now, why are you helping me?
- Why?

361
00:30:04,967 --> 00:30:07,606
Because I like you. I do.

362
00:30:08,487 --> 00:30:12,719
But I don't like the way that you say on
the plane, with your face scranched up,

363
00:30:12,847 --> 00:30:14,803
"You're French, aren't you?"

364
00:30:14,887 --> 00:30:19,517
I don't like the way you say, with your
eyes all squinty, "All men are bastards."

365
00:30:19,607 --> 00:30:21,598
Scranched?

366
00:30:32,207 --> 00:30:34,402
Please, don't break the car, OK?

367
00:30:42,767 --> 00:30:45,122
OK. So I try to understand.

368
00:30:45,207 --> 00:30:47,960
He tells you he has met this woman...

369
00:30:48,047 --> 00:30:50,197
No, this... goddess.

370
00:30:50,287 --> 00:30:53,723
He breaks your heart. He hu...

371
00:30:53,807 --> 00:30:56,401
Hurts me. Humbles me.

372
00:30:56,487 --> 00:30:58,478
- Humiliates you.
- Humiliates me.

373
00:30:58,567 --> 00:31:02,037
OK, and then you come here to Paris
so that he can do it again,

374
00:31:02,127 --> 00:31:04,118
but this time right in your face.

375
00:31:04,207 --> 00:31:06,357
No.

376
00:31:08,527 --> 00:31:12,520
No. I come to Paris
to get back the man that I love.

377
00:31:12,607 --> 00:31:15,565
Is that so hard to understand,
even for a person like you?

378
00:31:15,647 --> 00:31:20,198
- OK, and meanwhile his lover...
- Don't ever use that word again.

379
00:31:20,287 --> 00:31:25,042
This bastard woman,
she's feeling something else, maybe?

380
00:31:25,847 --> 00:31:30,682
Once he saw me, myself, moi, everything
would change, the spell would be broken.

381
00:31:32,167 --> 00:31:34,681
You don't think
I could change his mind? I could.

382
00:31:34,767 --> 00:31:38,157
I would remind him of our life together.
We had a pertect life.

383
00:31:38,247 --> 00:31:41,045
- Evidently.
- I've never been so happy.

384
00:31:41,127 --> 00:31:44,005
When someone says they are happy,
my ass begins to twitch.

385
00:31:44,087 --> 00:31:47,443
We had plans, OK?
We had plans for a home and a family.

386
00:31:47,527 --> 00:31:51,156
- I would remind him of that.
- He was obviously very attached to them.

387
00:31:51,887 --> 00:31:55,357
- If all else failed...
- You'd get down on your knees and beg?

388
00:31:55,447 --> 00:31:57,677
- It's possible.
- Now I can see it.

389
00:31:57,767 --> 00:32:01,123
There is the goddess,
standing next to Charlie, in her negligee.

390
00:32:01,207 --> 00:32:03,675
And you are there on your knees,
begging.

391
00:32:03,767 --> 00:32:06,361
Poor Charlie. Tough decision.

392
00:32:13,647 --> 00:32:16,684
- I didn't beg.
- No. You fainted.

393
00:32:29,247 --> 00:32:32,080
I see how far you'd go
for the love of your life.

394
00:32:32,807 --> 00:32:36,720
If you know so much about women, why
was no one at the airport to greet you?

395
00:32:36,807 --> 00:32:40,720
- Oh, please. I'm finished with women.
- You haven't found the right one?

396
00:32:40,807 --> 00:32:43,844
- I have found plenty of them.
- You're afraid of commitment.

397
00:32:43,927 --> 00:32:47,476
- I'm not afraid of anything.
- I know your problem. No staying power.

398
00:32:47,567 --> 00:32:49,922
- What do you mean?
- You can't stick it out.

399
00:32:50,007 --> 00:32:52,123
- It's obvious.
- It is?

400
00:32:52,207 --> 00:32:54,960
You are afraid of commitment.

401
00:32:55,047 --> 00:32:57,925
Commitment.
OK, sorry. I thought you meant...

402
00:32:58,007 --> 00:33:00,521
- What did you think...
- Nothing. Forget it.

403
00:33:01,487 --> 00:33:04,206
- This problem.
- It's not a problem.

404
00:33:04,287 --> 00:33:07,040
For you, Luc?
Every man goes through that.

405
00:33:07,127 --> 00:33:10,915
I mean, Charlie never did,
but it's usually an issue of self-esteem.

406
00:33:11,247 --> 00:33:15,479
It's just a very recent phenomenon, OK?
I've been under a lot of pressure recently.

407
00:33:15,567 --> 00:33:17,922
Soon, it will all be over.

408
00:33:18,007 --> 00:33:22,762
And then, zip, boom, bonjour!
I am back in business. OK?

409
00:33:32,207 --> 00:33:34,767
- Bob, great to see you.
- Hi, Luc.

410
00:33:34,847 --> 00:33:36,599
You've met my friend Kate?

411
00:33:36,687 --> 00:33:38,678
Hello, again.

412
00:33:42,607 --> 00:33:44,598
Where's the rest?

413
00:33:49,687 --> 00:33:52,121
What about my money and my passport?

414
00:33:53,767 --> 00:33:56,804
Forget the passport. He sold it.
First thing to go.

415
00:33:59,007 --> 00:34:02,636
What about my suitcase and my clothes?
Ask him about my vitamins.

416
00:34:03,887 --> 00:34:06,117
Her clothes?

417
00:34:06,207 --> 00:34:07,925
I gave them to Monique.

418
00:34:08,367 --> 00:34:11,120
- Monique?
- What? What did he say?

419
00:34:11,567 --> 00:34:13,558
He threw them away.

420
00:34:14,527 --> 00:34:17,041
Oh... God!

421
00:34:17,127 --> 00:34:19,800
Oh... man!

422
00:34:25,087 --> 00:34:26,725
What? No, thank you.

423
00:34:29,087 --> 00:34:31,806
You got rid of everything?

424
00:34:36,727 --> 00:34:38,718
Except for that...

425
00:35:00,007 --> 00:35:03,363
- You hid a plant in my bag.
- It's not just a plant. It is a vine.

426
00:35:03,447 --> 00:35:06,564
That's why you're helping me.
You don't give a shit about me.

427
00:35:06,647 --> 00:35:10,435
Look, I'm sorry you lost all your stuff
but it was not me who stole it.

428
00:35:10,527 --> 00:35:15,123
What if I had gotten stopped at customs?
Did you ever think of that?

429
00:35:15,207 --> 00:35:18,438
Don't be ridiculous.
People like you they don't stop.

430
00:35:18,527 --> 00:35:20,802
Why do you think I choose you?
Look at you.

431
00:35:20,887 --> 00:35:23,082
You would declare a pack
of chewing gum.

432
00:35:23,167 --> 00:35:25,158
Please, don't ever, ever...

433
00:35:26,807 --> 00:35:28,798
Never touch my vine.

434
00:35:29,647 --> 00:35:32,923
You don't understand. This is my future.

435
00:35:33,007 --> 00:35:37,478
With this vine, I'm going to make a great
vineyard and get out of this shithole.

436
00:35:37,567 --> 00:35:41,355
Donnez-moi un break. You can't make
a vineyard out of one vine.

437
00:35:41,447 --> 00:35:43,039
No, not one vine.

438
00:35:43,127 --> 00:35:47,598
I take this little American vine, mix it with
some others and I make something new.

439
00:35:47,687 --> 00:35:50,076
I don't care.

440
00:35:50,167 --> 00:35:53,921
