I have no money, no ticket, no passport.

444
00:36:06,647 --> 00:36:09,036
- Here. Take this.
- No. I don't want your money.

445
00:36:09,127 --> 00:36:13,598
- It is yours. It is what he got for your stuff.
- I don't want your money.

446
00:36:13,687 --> 00:36:16,599
Now go away. Stop following me.

447
00:36:17,767 --> 00:36:19,758
OK.

448
00:37:12,967 --> 00:37:15,037
What necklace?

449
00:37:15,127 --> 00:37:17,118
I didn't see any necklace!

450
00:37:17,207 --> 00:37:19,198
It must still be in her bag!

451
00:37:20,287 --> 00:37:22,084
In her bag?

452
00:38:58,887 --> 00:39:03,722
I see that you are a resident of Canada,
and are applying for Canadian citizenship.

453
00:39:04,047 --> 00:39:08,165
- My fiance is Canadian.
- Let me ask you something.

454
00:39:08,247 --> 00:39:12,559
You no longer want to be an American but
expect me to give you a new passport?

455
00:39:14,447 --> 00:39:16,324
Is this a trick question?

456
00:39:16,407 --> 00:39:20,685
I need to see your Canadian resident visa
before I can process your application.

457
00:39:20,767 --> 00:39:22,644
Next.

458
00:39:34,567 --> 00:39:39,436
OK. So, how it works is
I ask you a question and you comment.

459
00:39:41,567 --> 00:39:44,559
