469
00:40:20,247 --> 00:40:22,078
OK.

470
00:40:24,247 --> 00:40:29,037
Have you...
ever been convicted of a felony?

471
00:40:33,167 --> 00:40:34,156
No.

472
00:40:38,287 --> 00:40:39,879
Yes.

473
00:40:40,207 --> 00:40:44,883
OK. OK, I was at Ronny Templeton's
house and somebody handed me a cig...

474
00:40:44,967 --> 00:40:47,879
OK, I knew it wasn't a cigarette.
It was peer pressure.

475
00:40:47,967 --> 00:40:50,242
Peer pressure is terrible in college.

476
00:40:50,327 --> 00:40:52,522
Sure, I understand. See, the thing is,

477
00:40:52,607 --> 00:40:56,805
we just received this letter from
a Sergeant Patton at the US embassy.

478
00:40:56,887 --> 00:41:01,085
It says here that you were once convicted
for possession of a narcotic.

479
00:41:04,007 --> 00:41:06,282
Is marijuana really a narcotic?

480
00:41:06,367 --> 00:41:09,916
I mean, it was just the one time,
and I didn't even enjoy it.

481
00:41:10,007 --> 00:41:14,239
I inhaled, but then I was coughing
and I was hacking away for ten minutes.

482
00:41:14,327 --> 00:41:17,922
- I hate that.
- You do?

483
00:41:18,967 --> 00:41:22,403
Look, the point is that you didn't
include this information

484
00:41:22,487 --> 00:41:26,446
in your application for citizenship.
Paragraph five, article one.

485
00:41:28,207 --> 00:41:30,357
OK.

486
00:41:31,727 --> 00:41:36,517
This is where I tell you that your request
for a new residence visa has been denied.

487
00:42:30,527 --> 00:42:33,485
Yeah. He proposed to her.
He's such an asshole.

488
00:42:33,567 --> 00:42:35,956
I can't believe you won't be
my sister any more.

489
00:42:36,047 --> 00:42:39,357
- Do I have to be friends with Juliette?
- Lilly.

490
00:42:39,447 --> 00:42:42,962
Lilly, now stop it. All right?
He's not gonna marry her.

491
00:42:43,047 --> 00:42:45,038
Now, tell me everything you know.

492
00:42:45,127 --> 00:42:47,846
They're going to the South of France,
to her parents'.

493
00:42:47,927 --> 00:42:50,600
Then they're getting married
and coming to Toronto.

494
00:42:50,687 --> 00:42:53,121
We're not even invited. Not that I'd go...

495
00:42:53,207 --> 00:42:57,837
Lilly, now listen, OK?
This is very important. Very important.

496
00:42:57,927 --> 00:43:02,717
You have to tell me exactly
where they're going and when. All right?

497
00:43:02,807 --> 00:43:07,642
Now, just ask Mom, all right?
She has it all written down probably.

498
00:43:07,727 --> 00:43:10,685
OK. Are you still supposed
to be calling her Mom?

499
00:43:10,767 --> 00:43:12,997
- Lilly. Go ask Mom.
- OK.

500
00:43:13,087 --> 00:43:14,076
Mom.

501
00:43:16,367 --> 00:43:21,566
Kate? Is that you, sweetheart?
I've got all the information written down.

502
00:43:21,647 --> 00:43:24,719
I think you can still get him
at the hotel in Paris.

503
00:43:26,807 --> 00:43:28,843
Oh, my God. She's crying.

504
00:43:28,927 --> 00:43:31,043
It's OK. I'm not crying.

505
00:43:31,127 --> 00:43:33,357
I'm just...

506
00:43:33,447 --> 00:43:35,438
I'm just...

507
00:43:36,327 --> 00:43:38,636
I'm gonna get him back, Mom.

508
00:43:38,727 --> 00:43:41,878
I'm gonna get him back
and I'm gonna make him love me

509
00:43:41,967 --> 00:43:45,323
and we are gonna live happily ever after.

510
00:43:45,407 --> 00:43:47,841
And I'm just crying now in...

511
00:43:49,087 --> 00:43:51,282
happiness.

512
00:43:51,367 --> 00:43:53,722
Because I know...

513
00:43:53,807 --> 00:43:55,798
I know I will...

514
00:43:57,167 --> 00:43:59,158
I will triumph.

515
00:44:05,487 --> 00:44:07,921
- What do they call the beaches?
- La Cote d'Azur.

516
00:44:08,007 --> 00:44:10,043
- What does that mean?
- The blue coast.

517
00:44:10,127 --> 00:44:12,960
The blue coast, lying there next to you...

518
00:44:14,367 --> 00:44:18,918
- And we're gonna land in Nice.
- Nice? That's nice.

519
00:44:45,287 --> 00:44:48,279
Bob, you know how it works.

520
00:44:48,367 --> 00:44:53,646
If the little fish is to survive, he must tell
the fisherman where the big fish are.

521
00:44:53,727 --> 00:44:56,002
Forget it. I'm no rat.

522
00:44:58,207 --> 00:45:03,679
You're mixing your metaphors.
Who buys the passports?

523
00:45:10,527 --> 00:45:14,486
- Hi, there. C'est moi.
- Welcome back, madam, to the George V.

524
00:45:16,487 --> 00:45:20,036
It's incredible how you do that.
The words come out, "welcome back",

525
00:45:20,127 --> 00:45:25,326
but the meaning is completely different.
Is it a French thing or a concierge thing?

526
00:45:25,407 --> 00:45:27,523
As madam wishes.

527
00:45:27,607 --> 00:45:29,802
You did it again.

528
00:45:29,887 --> 00:45:32,321
Tell me something, because I don't get it.

529
00:45:32,407 --> 00:45:34,523
Do you enjoy being that rude?

530
00:45:34,607 --> 00:45:38,202
Because when you do that,
it just gets underneath my skin

531
00:45:38,287 --> 00:45:42,678
and it makes me... completely insane.

532
00:45:48,287 --> 00:45:52,121
Thank you, madam, for the fascinating
lesson in our cultural differences.

533
00:45:52,207 --> 00:45:54,596
It would not betray
my duty now to inform you

534
00:45:54,687 --> 00:45:58,202
that your fiance and his friend
are no longer our guests.

535
00:46:00,367 --> 00:46:02,961
Well, whose guests would they be now?

536
00:46:05,367 --> 00:46:09,326
The Carlton Hotel will have that privilege.
They arrive in Cannes tomorrow.

537
00:46:09,407 --> 00:46:12,285
Perhaps madam wishes
to catch the last train tonight?

538
00:46:12,367 --> 00:46:16,155
- I could arrange for a taxi very quickly.
- Yes, thank you.

539
00:46:31,527 --> 00:46:33,995
Bob, I'm losing my patience.

540
00:46:39,567 --> 00:46:42,081
A big fish just returned
from the United States.

541
00:46:43,887 --> 00:46:46,003
Luc Teyssier. Your friend, right?

542
00:46:48,847 --> 00:46:50,997
Ask him about a stolen necklace.

543
00:46:51,087 --> 00:46:54,602
He won't be hard to find. Take a look.

544
00:46:57,007 --> 00:46:58,281
You're welcome.

545
00:47:40,247 --> 00:47:42,807
I come to make peace with your people.

546
00:47:45,127 --> 00:47:47,687
So you're still after Charlie?
It is incredible.

547
00:47:47,767 --> 00:47:51,203
I admire your persistence.
It's so American.

548
00:47:51,287 --> 00:47:55,075
I am not an American.
I am a soon-to-be ex-American Canadian.

549
00:47:55,847 --> 00:47:57,644
May I help you with your bag?

550
00:47:57,727 --> 00:47:59,001
No. Maybe not.

551
00:47:59,087 --> 00:48:02,875
You know, I am feeling
some very strange emotions for me.

552
00:48:02,967 --> 00:48:06,198
Guilt. Remorse.
My self-esteem is rock bottom.

553
00:48:06,287 --> 00:48:08,847
I'm trying to think,
what can I do to say I'm sorry?

554
00:48:08,927 --> 00:48:10,121
Shut up.

555
00:48:10,207 --> 00:48:13,882
You haven't spent 60 seconds with me
when you weren't after something.

556
00:48:13,967 --> 00:48:16,322
- Buy, sell or trade?
- It is so true.

557
00:48:16,407 --> 00:48:20,798
I used you, a lot. You helped me to get
my vine and I left you with nothing.

558
00:48:20,887 --> 00:48:24,277
So now I ask myself, what can I
possibly do to make it up to you?

559
00:48:24,367 --> 00:48:26,562
And so now I am here for you.

560
00:48:30,047 --> 00:48:31,241
Typical.

561
00:50:16,007 --> 00:50:18,919
So I ask myself what I can possibly do
to make it up to you,

562
00:50:19,007 --> 00:50:21,760
so I buy this ticket, et voila, here I am...

563
00:50:24,047 --> 00:50:25,036
Quiet.

564
00:50:42,527 --> 00:50:45,166
You promise one thing,
you do something else.

565
00:50:45,247 --> 00:50:47,442
So why should I believe
anything you say?

566
00:50:47,527 --> 00:50:50,837
Because I have no reason to lie now.
Do I look like the kind...

567
00:50:50,927 --> 00:50:54,363
You look like the kind who steals
liquor bottles from airplanes.

568
00:50:54,447 --> 00:50:58,599
The kind who offers a girl a ride, then has
to steal a car in order to give it to her.

569
00:50:58,687 --> 00:51:02,316
- Who puts a plant in a person's bag...
- OK, I get the picture.

570
00:51:02,407 --> 00:51:05,126
Hey. This is a no-smoking compartment.

571
00:51:05,207 --> 00:51:09,166
OK, I stop. Voila! For you.
See, I'm changing. I'm growing.

572
00:51:09,247 --> 00:51:11,442
- We help each other.
- I don't need your help.

573
00:51:12,367 --> 00:51:15,803
Do you have a plan
for when you see Charlie?

574
00:51:15,887 --> 00:51:20,722
Still no? You are going into a battle
with no strategy, no armour, no bullshit?

575
00:51:20,807 --> 00:51:25,517
- I don't need bullshit to get Charlie back.
- Just a little. It might be handy.

576
00:51:25,607 --> 00:51:30,681
For me, bullshit is like breathing.
I stay. I help you. I promise, OK?

577
00:51:30,767 --> 00:51:33,406
Do what you want.
It's a free country. Isn't it?

578
00:51:42,967 --> 00:51:44,923
Is that Charlie?

579
00:51:45,007 --> 00:51:47,077
Can I...

580
00:51:52,527 --> 00:51:54,961
- How did you meet?
- At a party.

581
00:51:55,047 --> 00:51:57,277
I'd come to Toronto
on a teaching exchange.

582
00:51:57,367 --> 00:52:00,803
We started talking and I had
this feeling about him. The same for him.

583
00:52:00,887 --> 00:52:05,165
It wasn't exactly a thunderclap
or a lightning bolt. It was more like a...

584
00:52:05,247 --> 00:52:07,715
Light drizzle?

585
00:52:07,807 --> 00:52:11,595
You honestly never had that feeling
about anybody in your entire life?

586
00:52:11,687 --> 00:52:16,681
If I did, I would not admit it.
His chin looks a little weak, if you ask me.

587
00:52:16,767 --> 00:52:19,406
It doesn't and I didn't.
Why wouldn't you admit it?

588
00:52:19,487 --> 00:52:21,637
Why should I? Look where it has got you.

589
00:52:21,727 --> 00:52:25,640
Maybe if you did, you wouldn't have
that little problem we mustn't talk about.

590
00:52:25,727 --> 00:52:31,324
It's not a problem. It's just a temporary...
There is something in his eyes.

591
00:52:31,407 --> 00:52:34,524
- Vain. It is a word, no?
- It is a word. He has beautiful eyes.

592
00:52:34,887 --> 00:52:37,640
And he knows it.
You can see it in his smile.

593
00:52:37,727 --> 00:52:40,639
Not even a smile. A smirk. It is a word?

594
00:52:40,727 --> 00:52:43,287
Shut up. Is it a word?

595
00:52:43,367 --> 00:52:47,485
Two words, no? Why are you chasing
after him after what he's done to you?

596
00:52:47,567 --> 00:52:53,164
Because I love him. And I'm afraid
that if he doesn't come back, that I'll...

597
00:52:53,247 --> 00:52:58,162
it'll hurt so much that I'll shrivel up
and never be able to love anyone again.

598
00:52:58,247 --> 00:53:03,162
You say that now but...
after a time, you would forget.

599
00:53:03,247 --> 00:53:07,081
First, you would forget his chin
and then his nose

600
00:53:07,167 --> 00:53:11,718
and after a while you would struggle
to remember the exact colour of his eyes.

601
00:53:11,807 --> 00:53:14,526
And one day you wake up and he's gone.

602
00:53:14,607 --> 00:53:18,236
His voice, his smell, his face.

603
00:53:18,327 --> 00:53:21,922
He will have left you.
And then you can begin again.

604
00:54:39,087 --> 00:54:41,078
Charlie?

605
00:56:03,847 --> 00:56:08,318
I can't seem to get enough of this cheese,
and I haven't eaten this stuff in years.

606
00:56:08,607 --> 00:56:11,644
You don't look like you got much sleep.

607
00:56:12,847 --> 00:56:16,044
For some reason,
I just feel incredibly refreshed.

608
00:56:16,127 --> 00:56:19,085
I had this dream
which I can't remember really well.

609
00:56:19,167 --> 00:56:21,920
You know when you have a dream
that is delicious

610
00:56:22,007 --> 00:56:25,443
and you wake up
and you feel all kind of transformed?

611
00:56:26,687 --> 00:56:28,917
God, it's beautiful here.

612
00:56:33,287 --> 00:56:36,996
Did you know there are 442 official
government cheeses in this country?

613
00:56:37,087 --> 00:56:39,078
Don't you think that's incredible?

614
00:56:39,167 --> 00:56:44,161
To come up with 442 ways of classifying
what is basically a bacterial process?

615
00:56:44,247 --> 00:56:48,399
You prefer one cheese, one cheeseburger
and one restaurant to eat it in?

616
00:56:48,487 --> 00:56:50,955
I'm saying I like the cheese.

617
00:56:52,487 --> 00:56:56,082
God! What side of the train
did you wake up on?

618
00:56:57,887 --> 00:57:00,242
God, it's beautiful here.

619
00:57:02,567 --> 00:57:05,445
What's that face?
You don't think it's beautiful here?

620
00:57:05,527 --> 00:57:07,518
You don't think this is beautiful?

621
00:57:10,527 --> 00:57:13,917
- What?
- I was born here.

622
00:57:15,847 --> 00:57:17,838
Really?

623
00:57:18,607 --> 00:57:21,280
But this is so beautiful and so charming.

624
00:57:21,767 --> 00:57:25,043
It was too beautiful for me. I had to leave.

625
00:57:34,167 --> 00:57:36,158
Oh, God.

626
00:57:37,807 --> 00:57:39,320
What?

627
00:57:39,407 --> 00:57:42,240
- I'm gonna die.
- What? What, the cheese?

628
00:57:42,327 --> 00:57:45,842
Don't say it. Stop that rocking.

629
00:57:45,927 --> 00:57:49,044
- Stop the rocking.
- I can't stop it. It is the train.

630
00:57:50,007 --> 00:57:53,363
It's here. The mucus is here.

631
00:57:53,447 --> 00:57:58,237
- The mucus?
- The mucus coating the intestinal wall.

632
00:57:58,847 --> 00:58:00,838
Spasm! Spasm!

633
00:58:01,327 --> 00:58:04,637
No. Look at the scenery.
How beautiful. The cows...

634
00:58:04,927 --> 00:58:07,157
- Please, not the cows.
- Not the cows?

635
00:58:07,247 --> 00:58:09,238
No, I just ate that cow.

636
00:58:09,927 --> 00:58:13,078
Here it is. Here we go.

637
00:58:13,567 --> 00:58:16,798
Lactose intolerance!

638
00:58:26,167 --> 00:58:28,283
Jacques Taranne?

639
00:58:30,247 --> 00:58:32,317
I know you.

640
00:58:32,407 --> 00:58:35,763
Phillipe Cazal?

641
00:58:37,607 --> 00:58:39,245
Michel Desbordes?

642
00:58:39,327 --> 00:58:41,602
Listen, gramps, you don't know me.

643
00:58:41,687 --> 00:58:43,678
Leave me alone, OK?

644
00:58:50,607 --> 00:58:52,916
You are feeling better now?

645
00:58:53,007 --> 00:58:55,441
- Better.
- The cow is all gone?

646
00:58:55,527 --> 00:58:57,916
- When's the next train?
- Not for two more hours.

647
00:58:58,007 --> 00:58:59,998
Good.

648
00:59:02,007 --> 00:59:04,885
- I think I need to walk.
- No. Bad idea.

649
00:59:04,967 --> 00:59:07,356
You sit. We wait for the train. You rest.

650
00:59:07,447 --> 00:59:09,438
Gotta walk.

651
00:59:15,727 --> 00:59:18,161
Luc Teyssier! That's it!

652
00:59:25,607 --> 00:59:29,441
My stomach is so sensitive.
That's where I put all my stress.

653
00:59:30,807 --> 00:59:34,117
Beautiful. Gorgeous. Wish you were here.

654
00:59:35,447 --> 00:59:38,644
- How long since you've been back?
- About six years.

655
00:59:38,727 --> 00:59:44,085
- Six years? Is your family a nightmare?
- I don't really want to talk about it, OK?

656
00:59:44,167 --> 00:59:47,318
A healthy person is someone
who expresses their feelings.

657
00:59:47,407 --> 00:59:49,398
Express, not repress.

658
00:59:49,487 --> 00:59:53,765
In that case, you must be
one of the healthiest people in the world.

659
00:59:54,567 --> 00:59:57,877
You know what happens to people
who shut everybody out?

660
00:59:57,967 --> 01:00:03,087
- They lead quiet, peaceful lives?
- No. They fester.

661
01:00:03,167 --> 01:00:05,362
Fester? I am festering?

662
01:00:05,447 --> 01:00:08,245
Inside. Fester and rot.

663
01:00:08,327 --> 01:00:12,957
I've seen it happen. You'll become one
of those hunchbacked, lonely old men

664
01:00:13,047 --> 01:00:17,404
sitting in the corner of a crowded cafe,
mumbling to yourself.

665
01:00:17,487 --> 01:00:21,639
My ass is twitching.
You people make my ass twitch.

666
01:00:29,967 --> 01:00:31,844
Excuse me.

667
01:00:50,647 --> 01:00:52,638
Wait.

668
01:00:53,007 --> 01:00:56,556
- Who is that?
- It's my brother.

669
01:00:56,647 --> 01:01:00,003
- Your brother?
- My brother Antoine. Antoine, this is Kate.

670
01:01:00,887 --> 01:01:03,959
What's happening? What's happening?

671
01:01:05,367 --> 01:01:07,562
All of this vineyard is Antoine's.

672
01:01:07,647 --> 01:01:13,040
It has been in our family for three
generations. It is who we are, what we do.

673
01:01:13,127 --> 01:01:16,039
But for Antoine, I don't know...
He is always sober.

674
01:01:16,127 --> 01:01:19,517
- That's a bad thing?
- He makes the wine but never drinks it.

675
01:01:19,607 --> 01:01:22,440
You always drink it. Now...

676
01:01:23,327 --> 01:01:25,363
Why isn't part of this yours?

677
01:01:28,127 --> 01:01:33,076
My father, when he retired,
he left it to Antoine and me.

678
01:01:33,167 --> 01:01:35,283
But now it is all Antoine's.

679
01:01:36,287 --> 01:01:38,278
I don't get it.

680
01:01:39,607 --> 01:01:43,395
You see, to make a great wine,
you must have the soul of a gambler.

681
01:01:43,487 --> 01:01:46,445
You like to drink, and you like to gamble.

682
01:01:46,527 --> 01:01:48,677
Sometimes I would lose a lot.

683
01:01:48,767 --> 01:01:51,839
Sometimes I would lose to Antoine...
My dog, my first car.

684
01:01:51,927 --> 01:01:55,078
- This vineyard.
- This vineyard.

685
01:01:56,527 --> 01:02:00,076
It was one night. He got me very drunk.

686
01:02:00,167 --> 01:02:02,601
You must understand,
I owed him a lot of money.

687
01:02:02,687 --> 01:02:05,520
- But he knew what he was doing.
- What was he doing?

688
01:02:07,047 --> 01:02:09,607
I lost all of it. One hand of poker.

689
01:02:12,527 --> 01:02:15,405
You lost your birthright
in one hand of poker?

690
01:02:15,487 --> 01:02:18,160
I'm an asshole. What can I tell you?

691
01:02:21,327 --> 01:02:24,683
So that's why he hates you
and you hate him.

692
01:02:26,327 --> 01:02:28,204
That, and I...

693
01:02:28,287 --> 01:02:30,278
slept with his wife.

694
01:02:33,767 --> 01:02:36,486
What about your parents
and the rest of your family?

695
01:02:37,367 --> 01:02:41,360
No. There is nothing between us.
It is all over. Finished.

696
01:02:41,447 --> 01:02:44,678
- What if you tried again?
- No. It's not possible.

697
01:02:44,767 --> 01:02:47,759
They hate me. They despise me. They...

698
01:03:16,887 --> 01:03:18,878
Yes, thank you. All right.

699
01:03:19,887 --> 01:03:22,276
I'm very impressed.

700
01:03:23,807 --> 01:03:26,640
She's a friend, just a friend.

701
01:03:28,647 --> 01:03:31,525
Since when are women just your friends?

702
01:03:31,607 --> 01:03:33,598
Since I met her.

703
01:04:18,127 --> 01:04:19,719
I'm finished.

704
01:04:36,807 --> 01:04:39,446
Fester, fester, fester.

705
01:04:39,527 --> 01:04:41,882
Rot, rot, rot.

706
01:04:43,767 --> 01:04:47,157
Poor you. You had to grow up here.

707
01:04:48,247 --> 01:04:50,442
Show me your room.

708
01:05:01,167 --> 01:05:02,839
What's this?

709
01:05:03,567 --> 01:05:07,162
It is a project I did
a long time ago in school.

710
01:05:07,247 --> 01:05:09,602
What is it?

711
01:05:09,687 --> 01:05:11,678
All right, I will tell you but...

712
01:05:12,847 --> 01:05:15,441
First you must take some wine.

713
01:05:19,847 --> 01:05:23,601
Can you describe it, the taste?

714
01:05:24,207 --> 01:05:27,085
It's a nice red wine.

715
01:05:27,167 --> 01:05:29,920
I think you can do better.

716
01:05:30,007 --> 01:05:35,127
A bold wine with a hint of sophistication
and lacking in pretension.

717
01:05:36,927 --> 01:05:39,805
Actually, I was just talking about myself.

718
01:05:41,127 --> 01:05:43,595
- I don't know.
- No, you are not wrong.

719
01:05:43,847 --> 01:05:49,240
Wine is like people. The vine takes
all the influences in life all around it.

720
01:05:49,327 --> 01:05:54,082
It absorbs them and it gets its personality.

721
01:05:54,167 --> 01:05:56,044
Here.

722
01:05:57,607 --> 01:05:59,677
Smell.

723
01:05:59,767 --> 01:06:01,758
Rosemary.

724
01:06:06,887 --> 01:06:08,923
Some kind of mushroom?

725
01:06:09,007 --> 01:06:10,759
Very good.

726
01:06:11,287 --> 01:06:14,677
Currant, cassis, mint,

727
01:06:14,767 --> 01:06:16,439
lavender...

728
01:06:16,527 --> 01:06:21,476
They're all in the ground here,
and in the air. Now... taste the wine again.

729
01:06:25,967 --> 01:06:28,083
Close your eyes.

730
01:06:34,927 --> 01:06:38,203
The currant.
I can taste that right away and...

731
01:06:38,287 --> 01:06:40,926
from the brown bottle... lavender?

732
01:06:43,287 --> 01:06:45,403
Incredible.

733
01:06:45,487 --> 01:06:48,479
And you made this box?

734
01:06:50,447 --> 01:06:52,597
Incredible.

735
01:06:59,367 --> 01:07:01,358
Thanks.

736
01:07:32,007 --> 01:07:33,998
Whose house is that?

737
01:07:35,447 --> 01:07:38,837
It's abandoned.
No one comes here any more.

738
01:07:38,927 --> 01:07:42,317
The guy who had this place,
he gave up a long time ago.

739
01:07:43,167 --> 01:07:44,964
Look.

740
01:07:47,847 --> 01:07:51,396
You see this earth? It has been resting.

741
01:07:51,887 --> 01:07:53,878
Now it's good.

742
01:07:54,607 --> 01:07:59,397
Someday I'm going to buy this land
and I'm going to make a great wine,

743
01:07:59,487 --> 01:08:02,126
right here on this wreck of a vineyard.

744
01:08:05,807 --> 01:08:08,526
So you'd risk everything for this?

745
01:08:08,607 --> 01:08:10,598
Do anything to have it?

746
01:08:11,087 --> 01:08:13,237
Get down on your knees and beg?

747
01:08:17,247 --> 01:08:20,478
What makes you so different from me?

748
01:08:21,087 --> 01:08:23,999
Admit it. Not much.

749
01:08:25,847 --> 01:08:27,838
OK, I admit.

750
01:08:36,407 --> 01:08:38,523
It's beautiful here.

751
01:08:46,447 --> 01:08:50,360
I will help you get your Charlie back.
If you want him back, we'll get him back.

752
01:08:50,447 --> 01:08:52,438
Like I promised.

753
01:09:15,367 --> 01:09:20,680
How do you plan to buy that vineyard?
You must have some plan, some strategy.

754
01:09:21,527 --> 01:09:27,124
- I had a plan, but it did not work out.
- It didn't work out? What was the plan?

755
01:09:27,207 --> 01:09:31,166
I had... something to sell.

756
01:09:31,247 --> 01:09:33,442
Something? Like what?

757
01:09:33,527 --> 01:09:38,840
- Stocks, bonds, a little bag of plutonium?
- It doesn't matter. I lost it.

758
01:09:38,927 --> 01:09:43,523
You lost it? If it was me,
I'd have some kind of backup plan,

759
01:09:43,607 --> 01:09:46,804
something more than
just bullshit to fall back on.

760
01:09:46,887 --> 01:09:50,721
Something, perhaps,
maybe a little bit... like this.

761
01:09:56,647 --> 01:09:59,605
Luc... are you coming?

762
01:10:08,247 --> 01:10:09,839
Lesson number one.

763
01:10:09,927 --> 01:10:14,205
Before going into a war, you must
choose carefully the field of battle.

764
01:10:14,567 --> 01:10:18,082
Also, never let Charlie see
how much you desire him.

765
01:10:18,167 --> 01:10:20,840
Never tell someone that you want them.

766
01:10:20,927 --> 01:10:25,284
You see that? What's that pout?
Juliette did that. I remember it pertectly.

767
01:10:25,367 --> 01:10:28,359
The pout is one of the French
women's greatest weapons.

768
01:10:28,447 --> 01:10:31,280
- What's so great about that?
- It is provocative.

769
01:10:31,367 --> 01:10:34,757
It puts the man in a constant state
of excitement and anxiety.

770
01:10:35,087 --> 01:10:38,875
She knows how to say "yes" when she
means "no", "no" for "yes". Understand?

771
01:10:38,967 --> 01:10:40,958
- No.
- You don't?

772
01:10:41,687 --> 01:10:43,006
Gotcha.

773
01:10:43,647 --> 01:10:46,844
Now, most important.
When Charlie sees you,

774
01:10:46,927 --> 01:10:50,442
he will be expecting a big scene, a drama.

775
01:10:50,527 --> 01:10:55,647
You will not give him the satisfaction.
This will make him immediately intrigued.

776
01:10:55,727 --> 01:10:58,161
Luc. Look. Look what I found.

777
01:10:58,247 --> 01:11:00,317
It made me think of you.

778
01:11:13,047 --> 01:11:15,686
Monsieur Antoine Teyssier.

779
01:11:15,767 --> 01:11:18,361
How will you be paying, sir?

780
01:11:35,007 --> 01:11:37,726
When would you like
to have the wedding?

781
01:11:37,807 --> 01:11:40,924
- Next weekend.
- Next weekend?

782
01:12:22,007 --> 01:12:25,602
- Is there something wrong, Charlie?
- No. I...

783
01:12:25,687 --> 01:12:28,155
I swear I just saw Kate.

784
01:12:28,247 --> 01:12:30,636
I'm sure it's just your imagination.

785
01:12:40,447 --> 01:12:42,517
Tell me. What does your father do?

786
01:12:42,607 --> 01:12:46,680
Well, he's a doctor... like me.
Except he's a psychiatrist.

787
01:12:56,087 --> 01:12:59,318
- I'll be right back.
- Please, Charlie, sit down.

788
01:13:31,527 --> 01:13:34,121
- My parents are watching.
- I'm sure I just saw Kate.

789
01:13:36,327 --> 01:13:38,238
Come with me now.

790
01:13:45,247 --> 01:13:47,966
You really don't understand
a word I tell you.

791
01:13:48,047 --> 01:13:52,484
How can I help you win back this
ridiculous man if you act like a clown?

792
01:13:52,567 --> 01:13:56,799
It was an accident, OK? I wasn't
expecting to see him right then.

793
01:13:56,887 --> 01:14:00,721
Sucking up to her parents... in that outfit.

794
01:14:01,687 --> 01:14:07,159
And did you see her? Cutting her food
into tiny little chewable pieces like that.

795
01:14:07,687 --> 01:14:09,405
I saw her. She was...

796
01:14:11,007 --> 01:14:13,396
- She was what?
- She was...

797
01:14:14,287 --> 01:14:17,040
OK. I know what you're saying.
I'm not sexy enough.

798
01:14:17,127 --> 01:14:20,915
- No, I did not say anything.
- I'm supposed to be this pouty girl

799
01:14:21,007 --> 01:14:25,285
who says "yes" when she means "no"
and "no" for "yes" and I cannot do it, OK?

800
01:14:25,367 --> 01:14:27,835
Happy-smile. Sad-frown.

801
01:14:27,927 --> 01:14:31,044
Use the corresponding face
for the corresponding emotion.

802
01:14:31,127 --> 01:14:35,405
But you? No, you want
a mysterious, sexy, manipulative...

803
01:14:35,487 --> 01:14:38,126
- It is not me who wants it.
- What do you want?

804
01:14:38,207 --> 01:14:42,883
- I want you... I want you...
- You want me...?

805
01:14:45,767 --> 01:14:47,758
I want you to...

806
01:14:49,047 --> 01:14:51,561
make Charlie suffer.

807
01:14:52,607 --> 01:14:54,598
To be tempted.

808
01:14:55,607 --> 01:14:57,643
I want you to make him

809
01:14:57,727 --> 01:15:02,562
feel like, even though
you are right there in front of him,

810
01:15:02,647 --> 01:15:04,638
he can't have you.

811
01:15:07,367 --> 01:15:09,358
That's all.

812
01:16:38,647 --> 01:16:41,036
Luc?

813
01:16:46,807 --> 01:16:48,718
Do you...

814
01:16:52,447 --> 01:16:56,838
Do you think I still have a chance
with Charlie after what happened earlier?

815
01:16:57,927 --> 01:16:59,918
Yes, of course.

816
01:17:00,567 --> 01:17:04,765
And tomorrow we will turn
your mistake to our advantage.

817
01:17:05,167 --> 01:17:06,885
We will?

818
01:17:06,967 --> 01:17:10,277
He will still be wondering,
did he see you?

819
01:17:10,367 --> 01:17:13,723
You will be like a ghost, a phantom.

820
01:17:13,807 --> 01:17:16,799
And it will infect them, their rapport.

821
01:17:17,687 --> 01:17:19,917
Well, when do I confront him?

822
01:17:20,007 --> 01:17:23,795
Just when they are starting
to look comfortable again.

823
01:17:25,367 --> 01:17:27,278
Then you attack.

824
01:17:27,367 --> 01:17:29,881
- Kate!
- Hi! Hi.

825
01:17:32,327 --> 01:17:36,161
- Can I sit with you guys?
- But of course. Please have a seat.

826
01:17:40,767 --> 01:17:43,281
Pardonnez-moi. Pay no attention to me.

827
01:17:43,367 --> 01:17:47,599
- So... you must be Juliette.
- Yes, I am Juliette.

828
01:17:47,687 --> 01:17:51,680
Let me take a good look at the woman
who stole my Charlie's little heart.

829
01:17:51,767 --> 01:17:55,077
I did not steal anything
that didn't want to be stolen.

830
01:17:57,447 --> 01:18:01,565
She's smart, Charlie. And beautiful,
and probably great at everything.

831
01:18:01,647 --> 01:18:05,322
- Look, Kate...
- Relax. I didn't come here for a fight.

832
01:18:05,407 --> 01:18:07,284
Hello, waiter.

833
01:18:07,727 --> 01:18:11,436
I don't speak much French,
so bear with me. I'd like a sea breeze.

834
01:18:13,167 --> 01:18:16,239
French waiters.
If you're nice, they treat you like shit.

835
01:18:16,327 --> 01:18:18,682
Treat them like shit, they love you.

836
01:18:25,647 --> 01:18:28,844
- What?
- Nothing. You just seem so different.

837
01:18:28,927 --> 01:18:34,285
Well... Charlie, I'm going through
some sort of transitional thing.

838
01:18:34,687 --> 01:18:38,885
See, after you called, I decided to get on
a plane to Paris and get you back.

839
01:18:38,967 --> 01:18:42,277
- I hate to fly. In fact, I never fly, right?
- Yes.

840
01:18:42,367 --> 01:18:46,804
But there was no way everything I'd been
building toward would be destroyed

841
01:18:46,887 --> 01:18:50,846
because some pouty little-this is
before I knew you personally-bitch,

842
01:18:50,927 --> 01:18:54,283
wanted to steal a husband.
I bought the ticket, got on the plane

843
01:18:54,367 --> 01:18:59,680
and somehow made it over the ocean.
Then an extraordinary thing happened.

844
01:18:59,767 --> 01:19:01,678
What?

845
01:19:01,767 --> 01:19:03,758
Everything went wrong.

846
01:19:04,527 --> 01:19:10,045
So I was wandering the streets of Paris,
penniless, without a hope in the world.

847
01:19:10,127 --> 01:19:13,836
And, let me tell you, you can do a lot
of soul-searching in a time like that.

848
01:19:13,927 --> 01:19:16,805
I realised that I've spent
most of my adult life

849
01:19:16,887 --> 01:19:20,197
trying to protect myself
from exactly this situation.

850
01:19:20,287 --> 01:19:25,998
And you can't do it. There's no home safe
enough, no relationship secure enough.

851
01:19:26,087 --> 01:19:28,806
You're setting yourself up
for an even bigger fall

852
01:19:28,887 --> 01:19:33,165
and having an incredibly boring time
in the process. Sorry, Charlie.

853
01:19:34,007 --> 01:19:35,998
Thank you.

854
01:19:38,167 --> 01:19:40,283
And that's when I took up with Luc.

855
01:19:40,367 --> 01:19:42,039
Luke?

856
01:19:42,127 --> 01:19:44,038
Luc.

857
01:19:46,007 --> 01:19:50,603
Here he is. Luc. Come on over.
I want you to meet some great people.

858
01:19:54,207 --> 01:19:56,846
Luc, the lovely Juliette.

859
01:19:58,647 --> 01:20:00,638
Charlie, Luc.

860
01:20:03,007 --> 01:20:05,043
Sweetie pie?

861
01:20:12,967 --> 01:20:15,765
- What did he just say?
- I don't know.

862
01:20:15,847 --> 01:20:19,078
He doesn't speak much English,
but we seem to manage just fine.

863
01:20:19,167 --> 01:20:20,964
- You do?
- Yeah.

864
01:20:21,047 --> 01:20:24,676
I think it's that transitional thing,
you know, to help me get over us.

865
01:20:24,767 --> 01:20:27,486
That's probably what it is but...
what the hell?

866
01:20:27,567 --> 01:20:30,081
I love the sea, so beautiful...

867
01:20:30,167 --> 01:20:32,158
so mysterious...

868
01:20:32,247 --> 01:20:35,159
so... full of fish.

869
01:20:37,847 --> 01:20:39,838
What does he do?

870
01:20:39,927 --> 01:20:42,361
Besides what we do together?

871
01:20:42,447 --> 01:20:45,041
I don't think he does anything at all.

872
01:20:53,167 --> 01:20:55,806
That was so great.

873
01:20:56,687 --> 01:21:01,283
Hi, there. You were fantastic. Incredible.
They were completely destroyed.

874
01:21:01,367 --> 01:21:05,155
That was amazing. I just feel released.

875
01:21:05,247 --> 01:21:08,956
Now, tonight,
you will have dinner with Charlie,

876
01:21:09,047 --> 01:21:12,835
pretending to work out the details
of the breakup.

877
01:21:12,927 --> 01:21:16,283
By tomorrow, I promise you,
you will be queen of the castle again.

878
01:21:16,367 --> 01:21:18,801
We must celebrate.
Some wine, champagne.

879
01:21:19,687 --> 01:21:21,678
- Don't move.
- OK.

880
01:21:31,407 --> 01:21:34,843
A beautiful day to be in Cannes.
Isn't it, Kate?

881
01:21:36,607 --> 01:21:38,404
I'm sorry. Do we know each other?

882
01:21:38,487 --> 01:21:42,480
No. But we have a mutual acquaintance.
Luc Teyssier.

883
01:21:43,807 --> 01:21:47,482
That's why I come talk to you
about a... necklace.

884
01:21:53,327 --> 01:21:57,366
The necklace.
He was silly and he didn't declare it.

885
01:21:57,447 --> 01:22:00,803
Will it be a large penalty
that he'll have to pay?

886
01:22:07,607 --> 01:22:10,167
So why don't you just arrest him?

887
01:22:10,247 --> 01:22:14,843
I'm old-fashioned. I owe him a large debt,
much bigger than the debt of money.

888
01:22:14,927 --> 01:22:19,239
So I ask you to talk to him. It can be
returned to me tomorrow... anonymously.

889
01:22:20,327 --> 01:22:22,887
- He'll never agree.
- He must.

890
01:22:24,527 --> 01:22:27,280
Call me tomorrow.

891
01:22:27,367 --> 01:22:31,519
It really is a beautiful day.
I hope you're able to enjoy it.

892
01:22:42,007 --> 01:22:45,204
This is where I will sell
my necklace tomorrow.

893
01:22:45,287 --> 01:22:47,755
- Your necklace.
- My necklace.

894
01:22:47,847 --> 01:22:49,963
It was my grandmother's necklace.

895
01:22:50,047 --> 01:22:53,881
She lived in San Francisco.
When she died, she left it to me.

896
01:22:53,967 --> 01:22:56,037
OK, sure. Why not?

897
01:22:56,767 --> 01:22:58,405
Luc?

898
01:22:58,487 --> 01:23:01,843
- What if I sell the necklace?
- You? What do you mean? Why?

899
01:23:01,927 --> 01:23:06,239
Why? Because I am me, and you are you.

900
01:23:06,327 --> 01:23:10,843
- I mean, if I go into Cartier...
- All dressed up, looking just so.

901
01:23:10,927 --> 01:23:13,919
Smiling your little smile,
walking your little walk.

902
01:23:14,007 --> 01:23:15,918
That would be better. Thank you.

903
01:23:16,207 --> 01:23:20,166
- What do you mean, my little walk?
- Just the way you walk, you know?

904
01:23:20,247 --> 01:23:24,877
- Like a woman, but also like a little girl.
- No, it's not.

905
01:23:32,047 --> 01:23:34,686
You want something to drink?

906
01:23:34,767 --> 01:23:36,962
OK. Great. I'll be out in a second.

907
01:23:53,487 --> 01:23:56,285
I bought it at the store downstairs.

908
01:23:57,127 --> 01:24:00,676
You look wondertul. Was it expensive?

909
01:24:00,767 --> 01:24:03,327
- Yeah.
- You charged it to the room?

910
01:24:03,847 --> 01:24:06,077
Good. No problem.

911
01:24:06,167 --> 01:24:08,965
I only wish my brother could see you.

912
01:24:09,047 --> 01:24:11,083
It only needs one thing.

913
01:24:11,927 --> 01:24:15,886
- You will wear this tonight.
- I don't think that's such a good idea.

914
01:24:16,607 --> 01:24:18,996
I insist. It will be your charm...

915
01:24:19,087 --> 01:24:21,078
Your good luck charm.

916
01:24:31,367 --> 01:24:33,961
Who is the goddess now?

917
01:24:34,647 --> 01:24:36,877
Now! We practise.

918
01:24:36,967 --> 01:24:38,958
I will be Charlie.

919
01:24:41,847 --> 01:24:43,838
I'll be Kate.

920
01:24:46,087 --> 01:24:48,840
So we are dancing.
I realise how much I need you.

921
01:24:48,927 --> 01:24:52,602
I am thinking, I am an idiot,
a fool, a chinless, mindless...

922
01:24:52,687 --> 01:24:54,678
OK. OK, I get the idea.

923
01:24:56,087 --> 01:24:58,078
We are dancing.

924
01:24:58,167 --> 01:25:01,079
It feels... so right.

925
01:25:01,167 --> 01:25:03,158
Now, what do you say to me?

926
01:25:05,367 --> 01:25:07,562
I don't know any more.

927
01:25:07,647 --> 01:25:09,683
You don't?

928
01:25:09,767 --> 01:25:14,397
I don't know when to stop pretending.
I mean, when do I tell him that...

929
01:25:15,727 --> 01:25:20,278
That you love only him
and still you want him.

930
01:25:21,087 --> 01:25:23,157
You will know the moment.

931
01:25:24,407 --> 01:25:27,001
You will tell him, and that will be that.

932
01:25:28,367 --> 01:25:31,837
You know what I am going to do for you
to ensure victory?

933
01:25:31,927 --> 01:25:33,838
What's that?

934
01:25:33,927 --> 01:25:35,918
Juliette.

935
01:25:37,767 --> 01:25:39,166
Juliette?

936
01:25:39,247 --> 01:25:43,320
She will be feeling a little sad tonight,
a little angry.

937
01:25:43,407 --> 01:25:45,682
A little vulnerable.

938
01:25:45,767 --> 01:25:48,725
I will find her and I will... comfort her.

939
01:25:50,807 --> 01:25:54,117
I wouldn't want you to do
anything too unpleasant.

940
01:25:55,287 --> 01:25:57,801
- I do it for you.
- Well, what about your little...?

941
01:25:57,887 --> 01:26:00,924
My little problem
will not be such a problem tonight.

942
01:26:01,007 --> 01:26:04,443
Suddenly, I'm feeling like you-relaxed.

943
01:26:05,247 --> 01:26:08,603
I will go to her.
I will find her and talk to her...

944
01:26:13,167 --> 01:26:15,237
Let's just dance.

945
01:26:31,527 --> 01:26:35,520
I keep the bonsai.
The lamp we got in New York is yours.

946
01:26:35,607 --> 01:26:39,156
The love seat in the living room...
Tell me if you think this is crazy.

947
01:26:39,247 --> 01:26:42,717
We get a chain saw, right down
the middle and make two chairs.

948
01:26:42,807 --> 01:26:46,083
Can we not talk about this?
It's so depressing, isn't it?

949
01:26:46,167 --> 01:26:49,716
It's business, Charlie.
This is the business of breaking up.

950
01:26:49,807 --> 01:26:53,516
If you can't handle it, I could have
a yard sale and send you half the cash.

951
01:26:53,607 --> 01:26:56,883
- You must hate me.
- I don't. The CDs will be tough, though.

952
01:26:56,967 --> 01:27:00,323
- Why don't you just let me have them?
- You don't hate me?

953
01:27:00,407 --> 01:27:03,843
No. I did, Charlie. I really did, but...

954
01:27:03,927 --> 01:27:05,679
Now...

955
01:27:07,087 --> 01:27:08,884
No.

956
01:27:10,327 --> 01:27:12,761
Kate.

957
01:27:12,847 --> 01:27:14,360
I...

958
01:27:16,967 --> 01:27:19,800
- Sweetie, are you crying?
- No.

959
01:27:19,887 --> 01:27:21,878
No, no. I...

960
01:27:22,207 --> 01:27:24,880
You know, I just feel so totally,
horribly guilty.

961
01:27:24,967 --> 01:27:28,437
Listen, don't feel guilty
because I'll start feeling guilty

962
01:27:28,527 --> 01:27:31,087
that I made you feel guilty and...

963
01:27:32,807 --> 01:27:34,638
You know...

964
01:27:34,727 --> 01:27:36,957
Actually, that was the old me.

965
01:27:37,047 --> 01:27:40,278
Just feel guilty. Swim in it
till your fingers get all pruny.

966
01:27:42,967 --> 01:27:47,040
You're amazing. You really are.

967
01:27:57,167 --> 01:27:59,158
Kate.

968
01:28:00,367 --> 01:28:03,359
Will you dance with me? Just...

969
01:28:04,247 --> 01:28:06,886
One last dance?

970
01:28:08,567 --> 01:28:10,046
Please?

971
01:28:22,967 --> 01:28:27,358
You're right about his chin.
Sometimes I want to hit it.

972
01:28:28,567 --> 01:28:32,560
- He's a waste of your time.
- No, he's wondertul.

973
01:28:32,647 --> 01:28:34,922
So tender.

974
01:28:35,007 --> 01:28:36,998
Not like a French man.

975
01:28:38,407 --> 01:28:42,241
- You know what I mean?
- Yes, I understand.

976
01:28:42,327 --> 01:28:44,887
How could he do this to me?

977
01:28:45,407 --> 01:28:49,480
When I was younger,
this wouldn't have happened.

978
01:28:50,007 --> 01:28:53,602
He would be with me in my room
and she would wait all night.

979
01:28:54,087 --> 01:28:55,884
I can imagine.

980
01:28:55,967 --> 01:28:58,117
Look at me, please.

981
01:28:58,207 --> 01:29:00,198
Tell me what you see.

982
01:29:10,767 --> 01:29:14,396
You seem so different... but the same.

983
01:29:16,847 --> 01:29:20,237
And it's like somebody
turned a light on inside you.

984
01:29:22,567 --> 01:29:24,558
Why wasn't it me?

985
01:30:27,647 --> 01:30:32,323
- Is something wrong?
- No, in fact, everything is fine.

986
01:30:33,607 --> 01:30:36,917
Please forgive me. Please forgive me.

987
01:30:37,007 --> 01:30:38,998
I must have been insane.

988
01:30:43,887 --> 01:30:45,878
Luc...

989
01:30:47,047 --> 01:30:49,038
Kate...

990
01:30:51,647 --> 01:30:54,036
What did you just say?

991
01:30:55,727 --> 01:30:57,718
I said Kate.

992
01:31:08,767 --> 01:31:10,280
- Oh, Kate.
- Stop.

993
01:31:10,367 --> 01:31:12,278
Darling.

994
01:31:12,367 --> 01:31:15,086
Charlie, I said... stop.

995
01:31:16,167 --> 01:31:17,998
What?

996
01:31:18,087 --> 01:31:20,237
- Charlie...
- What?

997
01:31:20,327 --> 01:31:25,003
Why wasn't it you who turned on the big
Kate light that burns so bright now

998
01:31:25,087 --> 01:31:29,000
that you can't resist dumping
your new girlfriend for your old one?

999
01:31:29,087 --> 01:31:31,078
What?

1000
01:31:31,167 --> 01:31:34,045
12 hours ago, all you wanted was Juliette.

1001
01:31:35,007 --> 01:31:38,079
Juliette? I... She's wondertul.

1002
01:31:38,167 --> 01:31:40,886
Exciting. And...

1003
01:31:41,407 --> 01:31:44,558
When I met her, I wasn't thinking.

1004
01:31:44,647 --> 01:31:47,764
Sometimes you just do things.
You don't think about them.

1005
01:31:47,847 --> 01:31:50,486
You just need to do them,
do what you're feeling.

1006
01:31:51,647 --> 01:31:55,560
Maybe I was just... I was afraid.
Afraid of where we were headed.

1007
01:31:55,647 --> 01:31:58,559
You know?
I was afraid of getting married.

1008
01:31:58,967 --> 01:32:01,162
Charlie?

1009
01:32:01,247 --> 01:32:04,284
You weren't afraid of
getting married to her.

1010
01:32:17,807 --> 01:32:20,924
You know, no matter what
I might seem like tonight,

1011
01:32:21,007 --> 01:32:25,523
it's still the same old me from yesterday
you'd wind up with tomorrow.

1012
01:32:25,607 --> 01:32:28,838
The same old me
who wants the home and the family,

1013
01:32:28,927 --> 01:32:33,159
who wants to plant some roots
and see them grow.

1014
01:32:35,727 --> 01:32:38,480
Do you want to be a farmer?

1015
01:32:39,847 --> 01:32:41,838
Sorry.

1016
01:32:51,527 --> 01:32:54,724
There's just one thing
I don't want any more.

1017
01:32:57,767 --> 01:32:59,758
I'm sorry, Charlie.

1018
01:33:07,407 --> 01:33:09,125
Yeah, it's open.

1019
01:33:12,687 --> 01:33:14,917
Good morning.

1020
01:33:16,007 --> 01:33:18,396
Morning.

1021
01:33:20,607 --> 01:33:23,075
So how did it go? What happened?

1022
01:33:24,927 --> 01:33:26,918
Well, he wants to come back.

1023
01:33:30,487 --> 01:33:32,284
Congratulations.

1024
01:33:35,807 --> 01:33:38,446
What about you?
The old bull back in business?

1025
01:33:45,567 --> 01:33:48,604
We better get going. Cartier is waiting.

1026
01:34:20,647 --> 01:34:23,923
Everything as you said. The egg?

1027
01:34:24,647 --> 01:34:26,558
Nest egg.

1028
01:34:26,647 --> 01:34:28,922
It was wired from your bank in Toronto,

1029
01:34:29,007 --> 01:34:32,716
and Cartier has agreed
to issue the cheque in exchange.

1030
01:34:32,807 --> 01:34:35,196
The illusion is complete.

1031
01:34:38,447 --> 01:34:40,438
Thank you.

1032
01:34:41,487 --> 01:34:44,684
Why are you doing this?
You're not with Luc.

1033
01:34:45,007 --> 01:34:47,919
You will probably never see him again.

1034
01:34:49,687 --> 01:34:51,837
I don't know.

1035
01:34:54,367 --> 01:34:58,804
I must come to Canada some day.
You are very sympathetic people.

1036
01:35:00,447 --> 01:35:02,881
Well, I'm not really a Canadian.

1037
01:35:02,967 --> 01:35:06,642
In fact, I'm... currently without country.

1038
01:35:10,687 --> 01:35:12,837
Just out of curiosity,

1039
01:35:13,727 --> 01:35:15,718
what is it worth?

1040
01:35:16,847 --> 01:35:20,396
I would say... over $100,000.

1041
01:35:27,207 --> 01:35:29,596
44,782.

1042
01:35:31,167 --> 01:35:33,761
This is not possible.

1043
01:35:35,647 --> 01:35:39,037
Why did I listen to you
and your little walk and...

1044
01:35:39,127 --> 01:35:41,197
- He said there was a flaw.
- A flaw?

1045
01:35:41,287 --> 01:35:43,357
- Some flaws.
- Some flaws?

1046
01:35:43,447 --> 01:35:49,044
He said they were beautiful diamonds
but, officially, there are flaws. Sorry.

1047
01:35:49,967 --> 01:35:51,958
- It's OK.
- It's OK?

1048
01:35:53,247 --> 01:35:56,125
It is not as much as I was hoping,

1049
01:35:56,207 --> 01:36:01,361
but it is enough to buy the land
and to start the planting.

1050
01:36:01,967 --> 01:36:06,802
It will take longer, maybe six years,
before we have a decent bottle but...

1051
01:36:07,847 --> 01:36:09,678
Thank you.

1052
01:36:09,767 --> 01:36:12,804
Thank you very much.
You're my angel of luck.

1053
01:36:13,687 --> 01:36:15,757
Who would have thought it?

1054
01:36:28,247 --> 01:36:30,920
I have to go... cos Charlie's waiting.

1055
01:37:04,167 --> 01:37:06,203
You know I love you!

1056
01:37:10,207 --> 01:37:13,517
Listen, I had dinner with her...

1057
01:37:15,767 --> 01:37:17,917
Why don't you go back to her?

1058
01:37:18,007 --> 01:37:19,998
You went up to the room like a...

1059
01:37:22,087 --> 01:37:24,123
Juliette!

1060
01:37:36,967 --> 01:37:39,959
Ah, love. It's wondertul.

1061
01:37:41,447 --> 01:37:43,165
What are you doing here?

1062
01:37:43,247 --> 01:37:46,364
Some guy paid his hotel bill
with a stolen credit card.

1063
01:37:46,447 --> 01:37:48,438
I've taken care of it.

1064
01:37:52,887 --> 01:37:55,003
That's not true love.

1065
01:37:55,847 --> 01:37:57,838
What do you know?

1066
01:37:57,927 --> 01:38:02,045
Would you like to hear a true love story?
I know a good one.

1067
01:38:04,607 --> 01:38:08,600
- Really? Does it have a happy ending?
- I don't know.

1068
01:38:08,687 --> 01:38:11,281
Maybe you can help with the ending.

1069
01:38:11,927 --> 01:38:14,600
- Me?
- Yes.

1070
01:38:14,687 --> 01:38:17,838
Imagine... an airplane.

1071
01:38:37,367 --> 01:38:39,358
Kate?

1072
01:38:42,087 --> 01:38:43,202
Yes?

1073
01:38:43,287 --> 01:38:46,677
You are not afraid to fly any more?

1074
01:38:46,767 --> 01:38:49,884
You are thinking of
your little stone cottage?

1075
01:38:51,047 --> 01:38:54,437
It's on a hillside
next to a beautiful vineyard.

1076
01:38:55,527 --> 01:39:00,123
- But that's not what I'm thinking about.
- What are you thinking about?

1077
01:39:02,087 --> 01:39:03,566
You.

1078
01:39:10,367 --> 01:39:14,155
And I am thinking...
you should not be flying anywhere.

1079
01:39:15,727 --> 01:39:19,003
- I shouldn't?
- In fact, I am sure of it.

1080
01:39:20,087 --> 01:39:22,999
- You are?
- I am thinking...

1081
01:39:23,087 --> 01:39:25,521
I want you...

1082
01:39:27,887 --> 01:39:30,685
You want me...?

1083
01:39:30,767 --> 01:39:34,760
That's all. I want you.

1084
01:41:26,487 --> 01:41:28,637
- Sing that song.
- What song?

1085
01:41:28,727 --> 01:41:30,718
The Bobby Darin song.

1086
01:41:30,807 --> 01:41:33,321
- It's not Bobby Darin.
- Yeah, the Bobby Darin song.

1087
01:41:33,407 --> 01:41:37,241
- It's Charles Trenet.
- No. Somewhere beyond...

1088
01:41:37,327 --> 01:41:39,682
No. "La Mer". It is "La Mer".

1089
01:41:39,767 --> 01:41:44,045
- Maybe your guy covered it for Bobby.
- No. It is a French song.

1090
01:41:44,127 --> 01:41:46,118
Luc, could you just sing the song?

1091
01:46:08,167 --> 01:46:10,886
Visiontext subtitles: Julie Clayton

